{{infobox Chinese|l=Yin Water Pig|kanji=癸亥|romaji=mizunoto i|onyomi=kigai|p=guǐhài|w=kuei-hai|mi=kʷeɪ̯²¹ xaɪ̯|y=gwai2 hoi6|j=gwai2 hoi6|ci=kʷɐi hɐi|mc=kjwɨj ɣəi|oc-bs=kʷeʔ ɢəʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yin Water Pig also known as 癸亥''' (mizu no toi, kisui no inoshishi, kigai) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 60th (last) combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Rinxu|ja|壬戌}} and followed by {{ill|Koushi|ja|甲子}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Gui|ja|癸}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|亥}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和}}).

