'''Yin Water Pig also known as 癸亥''' (mizu no toi, kisui no inoshishi, kigai) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 60th (last) combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Rinxu|ja|壬戌|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Koushi|ja|甲子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|亥|1=Pig (zodiac)|lt=Pig (亥)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|lt=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|4=el|5=Ου Σιν|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}).

