In a {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦|1=Common Era|2=ja|3=西暦|4=zh|5=公元|6=es|7=Era común|8=nl|9=Gangbare jaartelling|10=simple|11=Common Era|qq=draft|qq=draft}} year whose final digit is 3 or 8 (when the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft}} are {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Bo|ja|戊|1=Tsuchinoe (戊)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), the month of {{ill|October|ja|10月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} is designated as the {{ill|month (calendar)|ja|月 (暦)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of {{ill|Kigai|ja|癸亥|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or to the {{ill|Seasonal Month|ja|節月|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (from {{ill|Beginning of Winter|ja|立冬|qq=draft|qq=draft}} until the day before {{ill|Heavy Snow|ja|大雪|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) as applicable.
