It is the 60th (last) combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Rinxu|ja|壬戌|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Koushi|ja|甲子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Gui|ja|癸|1=Mizunoto (癸)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, and the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Pig|ja|亥|1=Pig (zodiac)|lt=Pig (亥)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Water|ja|水|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}, forming a harmonious relationship ({{ill|Hiwa|ja|比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|1=比和|1=Wuxing (Chinese philosophy)#Harmonious Relationship (比和)|2=ja|3=五行思想#比和（ひわ）|lt=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|qq=Harmonious Relationship (Five Elements)|4=el|5=Ου Σιν|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}}).

